2052.subject: HPWE
2052.descrlong: Covers instruction and practice in the immediate and temporary care of injuries and sudden illnesses. Includes emergency response, rescue breathing, cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR), and first aid for adults only. Conforms to American Red Cross standards. Course completion encompasses written exams and skills tests for first aid and CPR certifications. (Offered as interest warrants.)
